And he speaks of all these things in the Church of Ephesus because the whole world and their paganism, not the whole world, but millions of people in the region would come to this temple and yet this great temple and yet Jesus and God would make this word that he's stating here.

48:49.640 --> 48:51.401
Oh, I got a temple that's way greater.

48:51.441 --> 48:55.825
It's my temple, the Holy Spirit, and then my temple living inside you.

48:55.845 --> 49:00.690
And grace to you in peace from God our Father and the Lord Jesus,

49:00.770 --> 49:01.311
Christ.

49:01.971 --> 49:03.393
We will be picking up on that.

49:03.994 --> 49:08.499
Should we continue in this next week or coming into the new year?

49:08.600 --> 49:23.698
I think we'll probably have another study or two in Ephesians to close out the year and start a new year, but grace always comes before peace in all of Paul's writing because you'll never have the peace of God.

49:24.386 --> 49:28.470
that your sin are forgiven, and that you're right with the Lord without the grace of God.

49:28.750 --> 49:30.872
God's riches at Christ's expense.

49:31.573 --> 49:44.065
And I close with Zephaniah 3.17, why we can rest as we started this, because he rest in his love.

49:44.325 --> 49:53.874
Zephaniah 3.17, the Lord your God in your midst, the mighty one will save, he will rejoice over you with gladness,

49:54.402 --> 49:56.725
He will quiet you with his love.

49:57.325 --> 50:00.589
He will rejoice over you with singing.

50:01.270 --> 50:03.452
We're going to sing one more worship song.

50:05.234 --> 50:10.900
I hope it starts, but I close with this.

50:17.107 --> 50:23.154
You know it takes faith, all of us, because I think we're all pretty much

50:23.554 --> 50:30.523
Made and wired about the same way, takes a lot of faith to believe that Jesus Christ is singing over you right now.

50:32.866 --> 50:36.491
When I sing worship, He's the object of my worship.

50:37.853 --> 50:47.465
But for my mind to grasp that He will rejoice over you with singing that God Himself rejoices in a singing over us.

50:50.529 --> 50:51.250
But it's true.

50:53.154 --> 50:58.420
And I might not rest in myself because I know myself.

51:00.563 --> 51:09.193
But if I'm going to look at this and say he will quiet you with his love, he will rejoice over you with singing.

51:09.253 --> 51:17.724
If he's resting in his love for me, then I know that I can rest in his love for me.

51:18.365 --> 51:19.726
Father, I thank you.

51:19.746 --> 51:20.747
I bless you.

51:20.767 --> 51:22.930
That you're singing over me.

51:23.330 --> 51:37.469
This is the position, the place that you've given me in Christ Jesus, the beautiful place and wording that you've given us, Lord, as we look at this personal letter.

51:37.509 --> 51:47.303
When you say don't take, when the world says don't take it personal, you cry out and scream out to us, take this personal.

51:47.923 --> 51:48.704
It's about you.

51:48.744 --> 51:52.850
And this position,

51:53.026 --> 51:59.394
that we are in Christ Jesus because of your grace of the cross.

51:59.474 --> 52:02.558
We have peace in the forgiveness of sin.

52:03.219 --> 52:11.910
And we can claim this promise that we are saints dedicated, set a part for you to enjoy.

52:11.930 --> 52:14.814
And the fact is that you sing over us.

52:15.134 --> 52:17.377
That is a amazing grace.

52:19.560 --> 52:21.522
Would you hear our heart in this worship?

52:21.922 --> 52:23.091
as we lift it to you.

